Oct 26 2008 	A hotel of note in any world-wide selection	We stayed 12 nights from 8/10/08. We had read some adverse comments but found them to be without foundation. It is an excellent hotel, an oasis of comparitive peace fairly near the city centre but with noteworthy restaurants, beach, pools, water features and a very friendly staff - all at a reasonable price for Dubai. We stayed in standard rooms (one in each) in Villa 35. Up - graded rooms are probably better but the standard room is certainly adequate for1/2 people.Any criticisms are very minor eg. no tea or coffee making facilities available in bedrooms. Buggies can be called to take one to a restaurant in the evening and home again. There is an influx of young people in evenings to party and enjoy themselves. And why not? They have a good time and do not interfere with the (mostly older) hotel residents. It is a 2 storey level hotel and lifts are not needed. We never used one.Taxis are cheap and on instant call - but get one with a meter! The hotel is a welcome contrast to some of the oddly shaped, high rise buildings in glass anr concrete. Mind you some of the concrete is nicely coloured! Whatever problems Dubai may have in the shape of heat, traffic and lack of notable scenery this hotel remains a perfect oasis. We would recommend it to all normal people!	
