Oct 31 2007 	We loved it here!	Having read some of the reviews of this resort, I was slightly apprehensive, despite the fact that my sister (who is based in Saudi) had stayed there on several occasions, and was happy to recommend it. We chose this hotel partly for its central location between the city and beach, and were perfectly happy with it as an easy point from which to explore Dubai, especially as we wanted a beach resort but didn’t fancy being so far away from the attractions of the city as some of the Jumeirah beach hotels turned out to be.While I have to agree that the rooms are a bit basic, and the décor is a bit dull and not as stylish as one might find in other 5 star hotels, they were very comfortable and clean – our balcony room (one step up from a standard room) was a good size, with all the facilities you would expect, and a lovely big comfy bed!The on-site facilities are excellent, and the food in all the restaurants we tried for evening meals was very good, although there were a couple of negative aspects regarding breakfast and lunch. 1. We stayed on a room only basis and paid for a buffet breakfast in the Taverna restaurant on our first morning, but although there was a good range of food we felt a bit aggrieved at being charged around £20 for 2 breakfasts although my husband only had 2 very disappointing cups of instant coffee. For the rest of the week I ordered room service while my husband went to Starbucks round the corner so we were happy!2. On days when we stayed at the beach we ate at the beach bar, and while the food itself was excellent and plentiful, there were only around 6 tables, which sometimes meant quite a wait to get seated, and despite the small number of tables, the food service was very slow.Those points aside, the resort itself has a lovely relaxed, informal feel, and contrary to what other reviewers have said, the staff are very friendly and helpful, and we had a thoroughly enjoyable stay here. The low rise villa accommodation set among beautiful gardens provided a lovely environment, which was very peaceful and tranquil (occasionally punctuated by the calls to prayer from the Mosque nearby, but that is part of the culture of the place).There was no evidence of building work within the hotel grounds, although I understand that the place has changed a bit over the years, so previous guests may have been a bit unlucky in this respect. Nor were we aware of any building or road works close to the hotel, although we did see quite a bit of this throughout the city – but it did not impact on our stay at all.In all, I would say to prospective travellers – think about what it is you want from a hotel. If you want somewhere posh, stylish and formal, then perhaps this is not the place for you. But if you want a relaxed holiday in lovely surroundings with an excellent range of facilities and friendly, efficient and helpful staff, then give this a go – we will certainly be back next year.	
