Mar 4 2006	Goodbye Dubai !	Dubai Marine Beach Resort and Spa. This hotel is situated at the very end of the Jumeriah Beach, sandwiched between the Dry Docks with its towering cranes and building works on the beach. The entire length of the Jumeriah Road has been taken up and is being relaid, widened I guess, although its hard to tell with all the jumble of things happening there. The consequence is that you do have noise on a 24/7 basis, although you cannot hear it in the grounds of the hotel, mainly because of its own construction noises either side. The Dubai Marine Resort and Beach is a little dated in the outer buildings, but nicely laid out grounds surrounding the apartments, which they refer to as villas. The Jumeriah Beach Hotel, some 6 miles along the beach is the ultimate in modern hotels, and worth a visit to the outside lift there as you get wonderful views for miles and miles. Dubai is a nightmare for traffic and jams, forget anything you get into back home, its 24/7 hell on earth if you hire a car. Avoid Avis in the hotel, seek out a much cheaper one in the yellow pages, or so we were told by the Avis rep, too honest for his own good. The shopping is not as good as we are led to believe. The shops around the hotel are some of the best quality, with the rest of the clothes not being to the taste of the english. Restaurants in Dubai offer excellent value food, often bringing two and three extra courses at no cost. If you go to the Oman, dont forget your visa and be patient, getting into the Oman is reasonably easy, getting out is harder, and takes a lot of time so you need patience and a high respect for the border controllers. Muscat is great, especially the Crowne Plaza, and that side of the land mass is warmer, the sea definitely warmer and very much cheaper. If you are going for three days to Dubai thats fine, but any longer you will be bored, after the gold souk and the dwindling spice souk, and trip up the Creek has lost its lustre. The jabal mountains are spectaculuar and dont miss Nizwar betwixt Muscat and Dubai, the delightful hill top village, with very cheap accommodation, on the way into town on the left, at £28 a night for the two of you. A tank of petrol £6. cant be bad can it.	
