Aug 24 2005	good value for money	we stayed at this hotel for 1 week and thought it was fab! its surrounded by tropical gardens and looks like paradise. we were right on the beach, and had no problem checking in as the staff were very helpful, we also got offered a nice cold juice when we first arrived at the hotel along with some cold flannels. The staff were excellent and friendly as i travelled with my partner and two children. i had no problem letting my kids wander around the resort as the resort was safe. we were approx 15 min from the town centre. but as taxi rides are soo cheap you can go anywhere. But dont take the silver colour taxis as they rip you off. always take beige/brown taxis. all in all the trip was good would definately stay there again.	
Aug 22 2005	A nice hotel close to the action good value for money	I was hesitant, having seen some of the reviews for this place to book here but my partner insisted it would be ok. It was- nice, comfortable, clean rooms, lots of great restaurants, 2 pools, clean beach, not massive but enclosed so children can't run off, friendly staff.... and close to everywhere you want to be. The traffic in Dubai is horrendous fortunately taxis are very cheap but we liked the fact that although we could easily get to places on Jumeirah Beach we were not stuck that far away from the Creek which is really cool and all the shopping and things of interest in the center. In some minor areas you could say its a little worn down but nothing too serious and its very clean. Plenty of sun loungers and space on the beach. The restaurants are great, especially the trendy sushi place. It gets very busy with people from outside on their weekend (thursday and friday I think if I remember right) and there is a great atmosphere. The rooms are away from this part though so don't worry about noise. The gardens are also beautifully kept, with water features and tropical flowers. Its not as glitzy or perfect or luxury as some of the other five star hotels, you do as always get what you pay for. We saved money here and so had enough to treat ourselves in some of the really luxury hotels restaurants etc! Its really good value for money and in terms of the price differential with these other 5 stars I don't think you loose out that much. Its very relaxed and made for a great stay. I will book here again when I return to Dubai.	
Jul 2 2005	Highly Recommend Dubai Marine Beach 	My mum and I stayed at this friendly, clean, delightful hotel at the end of May for 7 nights. The accommodation was spacious and clean and the staff were exceptionally helpful - nothing was too much trouble if you needed anything. The hotel boasts it's own private beach and we never struggled to find a suitable sunbathing spot or sunbed, in fact as soon as we started to put down our towel on the sunbed, a member of the beach club staff insisted on doing it for us - a total relaxation holiday. The restaurants on the complex were of a very high standard and there was plenty of variety. I would in particular recommend the Lebanese restaurant, something I was dubious of trying at first I admit, but what beautiful, tasty food, and again, the service was outstanding.There are lots of lovely hotels in Dubai, but my mum and I would certainly book this hotel again with no hesitation, in fact I already have the brochure for next year!	
