ve, food likewise, we are going back to dubai, well a tour of the U.A.E and when staying at dubai we are staying at the oasid hotel, some friends of ours have styed there and said it was fantastic, but in the middle of the building site, which the dubai marine beach resort does not have it is very secluded, which if you have a small budget your kids will not be happy, you will have to get a taxi everywhere, it is far to hot to walk!enjoy your stay in dubai it truly is a beautiful place!	
Jun 2 2005	Great Hotel	We stayed at the Dubai Marine Beach Resort for one week and I have to say that this hotel was excellent, the rooms were good size, clean and spacious, the impressive villas are surrounded by waterfalls, landscaped gardens, petit avenues with flowers and streams, the pools are great, the private beach is somewhat small in width but still very nice, there are some excellent resturants around the complex, which come alive in the evening and look great at night, Boudoir club is nice but was busy around the bar due to the free champagne on tuesdays, the hotel bar has piano player and a nice relaxed feel to it, the hotel seems to be very popular with non guests in the evening as they appear to flock to some of the nice resturants and club bars, it's a cool place to be in the evening with the young and trendy.The service within the hotel was top notch, we found them very polite and will do anything to help.This hotel is in great location because you are not far from all the shops and across the road is the beautiful jumeriah mosque which looks fantastic when illuminated in the evening.The hotel is 5 star and obviously it's not like the burj al arab or jumeriah beach hotel but this hotel has a lot more of a personal feel to it than the bigger hotels.I would recommend this hotel to anyone, don't be put off.Would definately go again.	
Apr 25 2005 	Steer clear of room 3205!	Having lived in Dubai for three years and knowing this hotel only by eating at their Thai Bistro and the Alamo Mexican restaurant (hotel bit opened just before we left for UK) we wanted a place to stay which was close to the city but had a beach, also a hotel that wasn't involved in the huge amount of building work going on in Dubai at the moment at the other end of Jumeira Beach Road, and this hotel seemed an ideal 5 star choice. However, on check in we were given the most awful room, number 3205, (broken curtain rail, wall safe broken, aircon not functioning properly, twin room but we ordered double) and it seemed to us that they were trying to fob us off with their only room available. Unfortunately we were checking in at 2330! We complained that night but decided to sleep in 3205 and complain again in the morning. The front desk manager didn't want to know and said we could upgrade to a junior suite at a cost of £50 per night, having booked for a 10 night stay we were not prepared to pay this extortionate rate and said so. We threatened to leave and asked them to prepare our refund in cash. Half and hour later they upgraded us to a better room without cost. After this debacle we spent a lovely peaceful holiday on the beach, the area this hotel is in is great as you can cross the road to visit some local restaurants which are very good value especially the Automatic Lebanese restaurant in the Beach Centre, that's not to say the food outlets in this hotel are bad, far from it! The open-air Italian is wonderful dining overlooking the sea and the Japanese lounge/restaurant is excellent albeit the service is a bit slow! But all in all we had a great time and would return for a second stay.	
