Mar 8 2005	Feb break in the sun	Date. Feb 26th 2005. Just returned from a 4 night stay at this hotel. We had a great time. We stayed in a junior suite which we found to be clean,spacious and comfortable. The grounds of the hotel were beautiful,full of greenery and water features. The beach was large enough for us and we had no problem getting a sun bed.We ate in the hotel most days and did not have a bad meal.We particularly enjoyed our meal in the Cuban restaurant where we were able to dance after dinner till the small hours. Lunch around the pool was excellent. The portions were huge!!We found the staff to be helpful at all times.The position of the hotel is great.Near the city and away from all the building. It is an older hotel and maybe could do with a face lift, but we had a great time and would go again.	
Feb 2 2005	Maybe 4 stars...	After reading the contradicting reviews about this hotel, I was somewhat prepared to find an average hotel. When making the reservation, I specifically asked for a non-smoking room with a king-sized bed. We got there close to midnight after a long flight and found ourselves in a twin room that was reeking of smoke. We were too tired to make a fuss, so we decided to spend our first night there. The pillows and blankets hadn´t been washed for a long time, because they also were reeking of cigarette smell. UUUggghhhh! After complaining to the front office, we got upgraded to a non-smoking balcony room. The FO staff was friendly and helpful. Obviously, only one of the villas is non-smoking. But beware, the cleaning staff smokes while they clean the rooms!!! So for you allergics, I recommend staying somewhere else. The balcony rooms are much nicer than the standard rooms, not so boxy and newer furniture. They are also more expensive, so I recommend you spend that money in one of the other chain 5 star properties instead. While the Ritz might be much more expensive, the Hilton Jumeirah is in the same price category as the Dubai Marine. The hotel has 2 small swimming pools and a tiny private beach. Breakfast was poor, room service extremely slow and the service at the pool was not very attentive. Definitively not a five star property!!! On a positive note, the location is very good. You have both the beach and closeness to the city. Then again, if you stay at e.g. Hilton Jumeirah, it will take you about 15 mins or so to get to the city at virtually no cost (taxi fares are ridiculously inexpensive). If you must stay at the Dubai Marine, try going to the (public)Jumeirah Beach Park, which is close by and much nicer than the tiny beach at the hotel. There are many restaurants within walking distance. The Mercado Mall is excellent and only 5 mins away by taxi.	
